If you want this function automatically determines the order of autoregressive and moving average orders and their parameters, then you donâ€™t need to provide arguments inside ARIMA(). The function will examine different models (combinations of p=0,1,2,.. and q =0,1,2,.., P=0,1,2,.. and Q =0,1,2,..) and return the one with lowest AICc.

Complete the following code to train an automatic ARIMA model on the data:

fit_arima &lt;- vaccine_administrated_tsb |&gt;
  model(
    automatic_arima = ARIMA(dose_adminstrated)
  )


